 Vasco Chaya LIFESTYLE WRITER chayav@dailynews.co.zw ZIMDANCEHALL star Jah Signal is set to unveil Bundu Series in conjunction with the Zimbabwe Parks and Wildlife Management Authority (ZimParks). This comes as the Sweetie (Shinga Muroora) hit-maker is currently touring tourist destinations in the country, courtesy of ZimParks. “The bundu experience will be coming on ZimParks social media platforms such as Youtube, Facebook, Instagram and Twitter among others. It is hinged on our experience in the bundu — Victoria Falls, Hwange National Park, Matopos National Park, Chinhoyi and Binga Sand Beach among other fascinating places,” Jah Signal manager Hillary Mutake said. The series is meant to market the country to both domestic and international tourists. “We have been filming all the places of beauty to market both popular and unpopular tourist destinations in Zimbabwe,” he said. Born Nichodimus Mutize, Jah Signal embarked on this tour on September 21, together with some of his Swaa Family members. “We have done the first phase of the tour, which includes Hwange, Victoria Falls and Chinhoyi among others. We still have a long way to go to complete the tour,” Mutake said. googletag.cmd.push(function() { googletag.display('div-gpt-ad-1588599181508-1'); });  The singer joined the music industry almost a decade ago and he made his name after releasing hits Unouya Rini and Sweetie (Shinga Muroora) among others.  Some of his popular songs include Sig Aenda, Kurisei Kughetto and Mubako among others.  Sponsored Links

